The paper discusses the use of deep learning and big data in predicting student scores, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of graph neural networks also suggests a potential connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and cybersecurity (cs.CY), as these fields often utilize graph-based models. Finally, the analysis of key factors that influence performance prediction could also fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
